Comments that are factually correct and non-offensive are often down voted.<p>Comment negatively about Google? Down vote.
Comment negatively about the risks of building your business on the shifting sands of startup SaaS? Down vote.<p>Ive never seen anyone manage to explain how it is logical to use the same action without any distinction, for any of the following, especially given the result for multiple down-votes is to effectively hide the comment from view:<p>- &quot;i disagree with this opinion&quot;
- &quot;this is offtopic/unrelated&quot; 
- &quot;this is factually wrong&quot;<p>The &quot;if more people upvoted, it wouldn&#x27;t be a problem&quot; excuse is not new, and as I&#x27;ve said elsewhere, it&#x27;s a ridiculous bandaid solution to a widely acknowledged problem.<p>If you need a pop culture reference, it&#x27;s the Walter White solution: &quot;our health care system is completely fucked, but this guy can make and sell illegal drugs to pay for treatment&quot;
